expression.expression: select [Dashboard_ids].[dashboard_external_id], lookup(dashboards, dashboards.[dashboard_name], [Dashboard_ids].[dashboard_external_id], dashboards.[dashboard_external_id]) as dashboard_name, lookup(dashboards, dashboards.[Owner], [Dashboard_ids].[dashboard_external_id], dashboards.[dashboard_external_id]) as Owner, lookup(dashboards, dashboards.[datasource_title], [Dashboard_ids].[dashboard_external_id], dashboards.[dashboard_external_id]) as datasource_title, lookup(Last_usage_date_dashboard, Last_usage_date_dashboard.[last_usage_dashbaord], [Dashboard_ids].[dashboard_external_id], Last_usage_date_dashboard.[dashboardId]) as Last_usage_date_dashboard, lookup(dashboards, dashboards.[folder_name], [Dashboard_ids].[dashboard_external_id], dashboards.[dashboard_external_id]) as folder_name, lookup(dashboards, dashboards.[tenant_id], [Dashboard_ids].[dashboard_external_id], dashboards.[dashboard_external_id]) as tenant_id, lookup(dashboards, dashboards.[LastUpdated], [Dashboard_ids].[dashboard_external_id], dashboards.[dashboard_external_id]) as LastUpdated, ''+ [Dashboard_ids].[dashboard_external_id] + ''as dash_url, ''+ lookup(dashboards, dashboards.[dashboard_name], [Dashboard_ids].[dashboard_external_id], dashboards.[dashboard_external_id]) + ''as dashboard_url_link, 1 as is_dashboard_exist from [Dashboard_ids]

select 
    final.*, total_count - unique_count + total_nulls as is_duplicate
from
(
select 
    'Dim_Dashboards' as table_name,
    count(d.[dashboard_external_id]) as total_count,
    count(distinct  d.[dashboard_external_id]) as unique_count,
    sum(case when d.[dashboard_external_id] is null then 1 else 0 end) as total_nulls
from [Dim_Dashboards] d
union all
select 
    'Dim_user_group' as table_name,
    count(d.[user_id]) as total_count,
    count(distinct  d.[user_id]) as unique_count,
    sum(case when d.[user_id] is null then 1 else 0 end) as total_nulls
from [Dim_user_group] d
union all
select 
    'Dim_users' as table_name,
    count(d.[user_id]) as total_count,
    count(distinct  d.[user_id]) as unique_count,
    sum(case when d.[user_id] is null then 1 else 0 end) as total_nulls
from [Dim_users] d
union all
select 
    'Dim_Groups' as table_name,
    count(d.[group_id]) as total_count,
    count(distinct  d.[group_id]) as unique_count,
    sum(case when d.[group_id] is null then 1 else 0 end) as total_nulls
from [Dim_Groups] d
union all
select 
    'Dim_Tenants' as table_name,
    count(d.[tenant_id]) as total_count,
    count(distinct  d.[tenant_id]) as unique_count,
    sum(case when d.[tenant_id] is null then 1 else 0 end) as total_nulls
from [Dim_Tenants] d
) final

-- list of Users per Groups, taken directly from MongoDB.
-- Exclude Everyone, Admins, All Users in System. those groups handled in the SQL below
select 
    fu.[user_id],
    fu.[group_id],
    fu.[tenantId],
    fu.[fake_dashboard_oid],
    fu.[fake_date_num]
from [Users_groups_without_admins_and_everyone] fu

union all
-- list of Everyone group by tenant
-- Each tenant has Default everyone group, which include all the Users within the tenant
select 
    u.[user_id],
    g.[GroupID] as group_id,
    u.[tenantId],
    '-1',
    -1
from [Users] u
left join [groups] g on u.[tenantId] = g.[tenantId]
where g.[GroupName] = 'Everyone'

union all
-- list of Admins group by tenant
-- Each tenant has Default Admins group, which include all the Users that has the following roles ['Sys. Admin' , 'Admin', 'Data Admin']
select 
    u.[user_id],
    g.[GroupID] as group_id,
    u.[tenantId],
    '-1',
    -1
from [Dim_users] u
left join [groups] g on u.[tenantId] = g.[tenantId]
where g.[GroupName] = 'Admins' 
and u.[role] in ('Sys. Admin' , 'Admin', 'Data Admin')

select 
    du.[user_id],
    du.[user_name],
    du.[user_create_date] as created_date,
    du.[last_login],
    du.[last_activity],
    du.[email],
    du.[tenantId],
    dr.[role],
    case 
        when dr.[role] in ('Sys. Admin','Admin','Data Admin','Tenant Admin') then 1 
        when dr.[role] in ('Data Designer','Designer') then 2 
        else 3 
    end as role_id,
    case 
        when dr.[role] in ('Sys. Admin','Admin','Data Admin','Tenant Admin') then 'Admins' 
        when dr.[role] in ('Data Designer','Designer') then 'Designers'
        else 'Viewers'
    end as role_license_group,
    case when DayDiff(currenttime(),du.[last_activity]) < 30 then 'Yes' else 'No' end as is_active,
    DayDiff(currenttime(),du.[last_login]) as Days_since_last_login,
    case when du.[email] not in ('SisenseSystem5W9mp','SupportAdmin') then 1 else 0 end as is_real_users
from
    [Users] du
left join 
    Dim_roles dr on dr.[id] = du.[role_id]

-- List of all dashboards shared by user and Groups 
select
    distinct d.[dashboard_external_id],
    d.[tenant_id],
    ds.[object_type],
    ds.[user_group_id],
    ds.[user_group_id] as group_id,
    ds.[shared_counter],
    ds.[fake_date_num]
from 
    [Dashboards_shared] ds
left join 
    [Dashboards] d 
on d.[dashboard_id] = ds.[dashboard_id]
union
-- This query retrieves a list of all dashboards shared by a specific group, generating rows for each user within that group.
-- fact_users_groups is a table which mapped users to groups 
select
    distinct d.[dashboard_external_id],
    d.[tenant_id],
    'user' as object_type,
    g.[user_id],
    g.[user_id],
    ds.[shared_counter],
    ds.[fake_date_num]
from 
    [Dashboards_shared] ds
left join 
    [Dashboards] d 
    on d.[dashboard_id] = ds.[dashboard_id]
left join 
    [fact_users_groups] g on g.[group_id]= ds.[user_group_id]
where ds.[object_type] = 'group'

select 
    du.[user_id],
    du.[user_name],
    du.[last_activity],
    du.[role_id],
    dr.[role],
    'Users' as Source,
    case when du.[last_activity] is not null then 1 else 0 end as is_active
from
    [Users] du
left join 
    Dim_roles dr on dr.[id] = du.[role_id]
union all
select 
    g.[GroupID],
    g.[GroupName],
    g.[last_update],
    g.[roleId],
    'Group' as role,
    'Groups' as Source,
    case when g.[last_update] is not null then 1 else 0 end
from 
    Groups g

select  
    u.[dashboardId],
    max(u.timestamp) as last_usage_dashbaord
from 
    Usage u
group by u.[dashboardId]

select
    u.[userId] as user_id,
    u.[dashboardId] as dashboard_external_id,
    dd.[tenant_id], -- May contain Null values as dashboards might have been deleted but still appear in the Usage CSV
    u.[userId],
    '-1' as fake_group_id,
    --u.[timeStamp],
    (GetYear(u.[timeStamp]) * 10000 + GetMonth(u.[timeStamp]) * 100 + GetDay(u.[timeStamp])) as datenum,
    1 as counter,
    case when du.[role_license_group] in ('Viewers') then 1 else 0 end as is_viewer_usage
from
    [Usage] u
left join [Dim_Dashboards] dd on dd.[dashboard_external_id] = u.[dashboardId]
left join [Dim_users] du on du.[user_id] = u.[userId]
where 
    u.[dashboardId] is not null

configOptions.importQuery:
SELECT
    GRP."_id" AS group_id,
    GRP."name" AS group_name
FROM
    "prismWebDB"."groups" GRP

SELECT 
    t."_id" as tenant_id, 
    t."name" as tenant_name,
    t."default" as tenant_default, 
    t."systemManagement" as is_system_management
FROM "prismWebDB"."tenants" t

SELECT
    GRP."_id" AS GroupID,
    GRP."name" AS GroupName,
    GRP.lastUpdated as last_update,
    GRP.roleId,
    GRP.tenantid
FROM
    "prismWebDB"."groups" GRP

SELECT
    U._id AS user_id,
    U."userName" AS user_name,
    U."lastLogin" as last_login,
    U."lastActivity" AS last_activity,
    U."roleId" AS role_id,
    U."created" as user_create_date,
    U."email",
    U."tenantid"
FROM
    "prismWebDB"."users" U

SELECT 
    ds._id as dashboard_id,
    ds.type as object_type,
    ds.shareid as user_group_id,
    1 as shared_counter,
    -1 as fake_date_num
FROM "prismWebDB"."dashboards_shares" ds

SELECT     
    D._id AS dashboard_id,
    D.oid AS dashboard_external_id,
    D."title" AS dashboard_name,
    D.datasource_title,
    U."userName" AS Owner,
    T.name as folder_name,
    D.created as dashboard_create_date,
    D.LastUpdated,
    D.tenantId as tenant_id
FROM "prismWebDB"."dashboards" D
JOIN "prismWebDB"."users" U ON D.Owner = U._id
LEFT JOIN "prismWebDB"."tags" T ON D."parentFolder" = T.oid

select
    ug._id as user_id,
    ug.users_groups as user_group,
    g.name as group_name,
    g._id as group_id,
    g."tenantId",
    '-1' as fake_dashboard_oid,
	-1 as fake_date_num
from
    users_groups ug
left join
    groups g
on g._id = ug.users_groups
where g.name not in ('Everyone','Admin')

select
    ug._id as user_id,
    ug.users_groups as user_group,
    g.name as group_name,
    g."tenantId"
from
    users_groups ug
left join
    groups g
on g._id = ug.users_groups
where g.name not in ('Everyone','Admins')
